+### 3.83 FR-E83: Journal Snapshots and Crash-Safe Compaction
+
+- **Description:** `journal.jsonl` supports embedded `state_snapshot` events
+  and a compaction operation that replaces an old replay prefix with one
+  snapshot record. The snapshot payload has `snapshot_version: 1`, the complete
+  replayed run model, and `events_covered`. Journals without snapshots replay
+  exactly as before.
+- **Tasks:** [REF:task:2026-06-journal-snapshots-compaction | journal-snapshots-compaction]
+- **Motivation:** FR-E69 made replay linear in journal size. Long autonomous
+  runs can accumulate enough lifecycle facts that restart/recovery cost grows
+  without bound. Snapshots cap replay cost while keeping the single-file
+  durable recovery contract.
+- **Decision:**
+  - Replay uses `src/state/run-journal.ts` only. If snapshots exist, replay
+    seeds from the latest supported snapshot and applies only subsequent
+    events.
+  - A `state_snapshot.snapshot_version` greater than the supported version
+    fails replay with a clear error naming the journal path and version.
+  - Compaction protocol is fixed: replay current journal, write
+    `journal.jsonl.tmp` with one snapshot and zero tail events, fsync tmp,
+    copy current journal to `journal.jsonl.bak`, then atomically rename tmp
+    over `journal.jsonl`.
+  - Manual compaction refuses live runs and corrupt non-tail journals. Engine
+    auto-compaction runs only while owning the active run and only after node
+    completion.
+  - `settings.journal_compaction_threshold_events` is a non-negative integer;
+    default is `1000`; `0` disables auto-compaction.
+  - Manual CLI:
+    `flowai-workflow runs compact --workflow <dir> --run <runId> [--dry-run]`.
+- **Acceptance criteria:**
+  - **Tests:** `lifecycle-replay_test.ts`, `config_test.ts`,
+    `engine_test.ts`, `cli_test.ts` (FR-E83; regression-locked; snapshot
+    equivalence, suffix-only replay, torn-tail tolerance, crash injection,
+    live/corrupt refusal, threshold validation, node-boundary auto trigger,
+    dry-run no-op, exact summary format, help listing).
+  - [x] Full project check passes.
