+# engine: Journal snapshots with crash-safe compaction
+
+## Goal
+
+Add journal-embedded run-state snapshots and a crash-safe compaction operation
+so long runs replay from a bounded suffix while preserving the durable
+`journal.jsonl` recovery contract.
+
+## Overview
+
+### Context
+
+FR-E69 made `journal.jsonl` the canonical recovery surface and explicitly
+deferred snapshots and compaction. Long runs now need that deferred capability:
+the journal must support `state_snapshot` events, replay from the latest valid
+snapshot, and compact old prefixes without ever leaving an unreplayable file.
+
+### Current State
+
+- `src/state/run-journal.ts` owns journal writing and replay.
+- Replay currently starts from `run_started`, applies every unique event, and
+  tolerates only a malformed trailing line.
+- The engine opens a `RunJournalWriter`, appends bootstrap and lifecycle facts,
+  and resumes by replaying the full journal.
+- CLI subcommands live in `src/cli.ts`; run-control helpers already reuse state
+  path and lock helpers.
+- Config defaults and validation live in `src/config/config.ts`.
+
+### Constraints
+
+- Keep `src/state/run-journal.ts` the single replay source.
+- Preserve old journals with no snapshots.
+- Refuse unsupported future snapshot versions clearly.
+- Compaction protocol order is fixed: replay, tmp snapshot write, fsync tmp,
+  backup copy, atomic rename.
+- Manual and automatic compaction must share the same implementation.
+- Automatic compaction only runs after node completion.
+- No new dependencies.
+- Do not call `gh`; push only to the local `origin` benchmark remote.
+
+## Definition of Done
+
+- [x] FR-E83: `state_snapshot` event carries `snapshot_version: 1`, full
+      replayed run model, and `events_covered`; replay refuses newer snapshot
+      versions with journal path and version. Test:
+      `src/state/lifecycle-replay_test.ts::FR-E83 snapshot round-trip equivalence`;
+      Evidence: `deno task check`.
+- [x] FR-E83: replay seeds from the latest snapshot, applies only suffix
+      events, remains byte-equivalent to full replay, and tolerates a torn line
+      immediately after a snapshot. Test:
+      `src/state/lifecycle-replay_test.ts::FR-E83 suffix-only replay touches only snapshot and tail`;
+      `src/state/lifecycle-replay_test.ts::FR-E83 compacted journal tolerates torn tail after snapshot`;
+      Evidence: `deno task check`.
+- [x] FR-E83: shared compaction follows the fixed crash-safe protocol, keeps
+      one `journal.jsonl.bak`, refuses active live runs, and refuses corrupt
+      non-tail journals without modification. Test:
+      `src/state/lifecycle-replay_test.ts::FR-E83 compaction crash injection preserves replay`;
+      `src/state/lifecycle-replay_test.ts::FR-E83 compaction refuses live run`;
+      `src/state/lifecycle-replay_test.ts::FR-E83 compaction refuses corrupt journal`;
+      Evidence: `deno task check`.
+- [x] FR-E83: `journal_compaction_threshold_events` is validated as a
+      non-negative integer, defaults to a documented non-zero value, and is
+      covered by config drift tests. Test:
+      `src/config/config_test.ts::FR-E83 journal compaction threshold validates and cascades`;
+      Evidence: `deno task check`.
+- [x] FR-E83: engine auto-compacts only at node-completion boundaries when
+      events since the latest snapshot exceed threshold and emits one verbose
+      line. Test:
+      `src/engine/engine_test.ts::FR-E83 auto compaction runs only after node completion`;
+      Evidence: `deno task check`.
+- [x] FR-E83: `flowai-workflow runs compact --workflow <dir> --run <runId>
+      [--dry-run]` supports dry-run no-op stats, exact success summary,
+      one-line non-stack errors, and help text. Test:
+      `src/cli_test.ts::FR-E83 runs compact dry-run is no-op`;
+      `src/cli_test.ts::FR-E83 runs compact exact success summary`;
+      `src/cli_test.ts::FR-E83 help lists runs compact`;
+      Evidence: `deno task check`.
+- [x] FR-E83: SRS and SDS document snapshots, replay, compaction protocol,
+      config field, and CLI command. Test:
+      `documents/requirements-engine/01-execution-model.md::FR-E83`;
+      `documents/design-engine/04-data-and-logic.md::Journal compaction`;
+      Evidence: `deno task check`.
+- [x] FR-E83: Full project gate passes. Test: `deno task check`. Evidence:
+      `deno task check`.
+
+## Solution
+
+### Selected Variant
+
+Use the architecturally correct variant: extend `run-journal.ts` as the single
+replay and compaction source, add a shared compaction API, invoke it from both
+the CLI and the engine's node-completion path, and keep config validation in
+the existing defaults cascade.
+
+Non-interactive rationale: this is the only variant that satisfies all hard
+requirements without introducing speculative storage abstractions.
+
+### Files to Modify
+
+- `src/types.ts`
+  - Add `state_snapshot` to the journal event union.
+  - Add config field `journal_compaction_threshold_events` on workflow
+    defaults and node settings only if existing settings cascade requires it;
+    keep it settings-level per task wording.
+  - Add result types for compaction summaries and dry-run stats if needed.
+- `src/state/run-journal.ts`
+  - Extend replay to locate the latest valid snapshot, seed state from it, and
+    deduplicate/apply suffix events only.
+  - Keep old no-snapshot replay unchanged.
+  - Add `compactRunJournal()` and `dryRunJournalCompaction()` using
+    `getJournalPath()`, `parseJournal()`, replay, and `Deno.FsFile.sync()`.
+  - Add a test-only crash hook after each protocol step.
+  - Refuse live locks via `isRunLive(workflowDir, runId)`.
+- `src/config/config.ts`
+  - Add default threshold, non-negative integer validation, and cascade.
+  - Include the field in settings key allowlists and default extraction.
+- `src/engine/engine.ts`
+  - Track event counts at node-completion boundaries.
+  - Trigger shared compaction when `eventsSinceSnapshot > threshold`.
+  - Emit one verbose/status line for the trigger.
+- `src/cli.ts`
+  - Add `runs compact --workflow <dir> --run <runId> [--dry-run]`.
+  - Follow existing manual argument parsing style.
+  - Print exact success line and one-line errors.
+  - Add help text.
+- Tests:
+  - `src/state/lifecycle-replay_test.ts`
+  - `src/config/config_test.ts`
+  - `src/engine/engine_test.ts`
+  - `src/cli_test.ts`
+- Docs:
+  - `documents/requirements-engine.md`
+  - `documents/requirements-engine/01-execution-model.md`
+  - `documents/design-engine/04-data-and-logic.md`
+  - `documents/index.md`
+
+### Implementation Approach
+
+1. RED: add state journal tests for snapshot equivalence, suffix-only parse
+   count, torn tail after snapshot, crash injection, live-run refusal, and
+   corrupt-journal refusal.
+2. GREEN: implement snapshot event types, replay seeding, compaction protocol,
+   dry-run stats, and clear errors.
+3. RED: add config tests for threshold default, zero disable, invalid negative,
+   invalid non-integer, and cascade.
+4. GREEN: add settings field validation/defaulting.
+5. RED: add CLI tests for argument parsing, dry-run no-op, exact summary, and
+   help text.
+6. GREEN: add `runs compact` subcommand with shared compaction calls.
+7. RED: add engine boundary test proving auto compaction is called only after
+   node completion and threshold crossing.
+8. GREEN: wire engine auto compaction using the shared API.
+9. REFACTOR: keep parsing and path logic centralized; avoid duplicated journal
+   path construction.
+10. CHECK: run focused tests as needed, then `deno task check`.
+
+### Error Handling Strategy
+
+- Unsupported snapshot versions throw `Unsupported journal state_snapshot
+  version <N> in <path>`.
+- Malformed non-tail lines fail replay and make compaction refuse before any
+  tmp, backup, or rename change.
+- Active live lock refusal returns a clear one-line CLI error and leaves files
+  unchanged.
+- Crash hook errors are test-only and simulate process abort at each protocol
+  boundary; every injected state must leave old or new journal replayable.
+
+### Verification Commands
+
+- `deno task test -- --filter "FR-E83"`
+- `deno task check`
+
+## Critique
+
+1. Snapshot payload must include enough data to resume replay without original
+   bootstrap records, including node declarations and directory declarations.
+2. `events_covered` must count pre-deduplication journal events, not only
+   unique events, otherwise compacted summaries drift from file size reality.
+3. Automatic compaction must not run while the writer still has stale sequence
+   state, or later appends may reuse sequence numbers.
+4. The CLI exact summary requires measuring bytes after rename, not estimating
+   from the tmp string.
+
+## Refinements
+
+- Applied 4 critique items: the Solution now requires full replay payload,
+  explicit `events_covered` semantics, writer sequence refresh after
+  compaction, and post-rename byte measurement.
+
+## Follow-ups
+
+- Multi-generation backup retention is out of scope.
+- Compression or binary snapshot encoding is out of scope.
+
+## Review
+
+## Review: Approve
+
+- Scope checked against TASK.md requested behavior and constraints.
+- Evidence: `deno task check` passed on 2026-06-12.
+- Residual risk: `deno doc --lint` still prints pre-existing npm type
+  resolution warnings for MCP SDK paths, but the project gate treats them as
+  warnings and passes.
